# Example environment configuration for the offline weather PWA.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored) and replace the placeholder
# values with the four locations you actually want to see on the home screen.
# `.env.local` is loaded automatically by Vite at build time and is NEVER
# committed (see .gitignore + CLAUDE.md > Configuration > "Never commit real
# locations to the repo").
#
# Format: a single-line JSON array of {"name", "lat", "lon"} objects. The app
# expects exactly four entries for the default slots; extras are ignored, fewer
# render as fewer cards. `name` is a non-empty string, `lat` is in [-90, 90],
# `lon` is in [-180, 180].
#
# The placeholders below are intentionally fictional — DO NOT commit your real
# coordinates anywhere in the repository.

VITE_DEFAULT_LOCATIONS=[{"name":"City One","lat":0,"lon":0},{"name":"City Two","lat":0,"lon":0},{"name":"City Three","lat":0,"lon":0},{"name":"City Four","lat":0,"lon":0}]
